{"key":"processedPost-10427763","value":{"id":10427763,"first":10427659,"last":10512650,"when":1243748999,"utime":"05/31/09 08:49 AM","content":"Evaporation of moisture from the substrate is the number ONE pinning trigger.&nbsp; Sometimes we say the same thing in a different way that fresh air exchange is the number 1 pinning trigger.&nbsp; Either way, lots of fresh air causes a loss of substrate moisture, and this is the biggest stimulation factor in a good pinset.&nbsp; A wet or water logged substrate will perform poorly.&nbsp; You want your substrate to begin to dry out, and then to re-moisten it.&nbsp; This ebb and flow of moisture content is far superior to a steady state moisture level.<br />RR","title":"Re: BEST fruiting chamber ever?"}}